{"ID":270321, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"321\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs320.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs322.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 321<\/div>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Covenants of the Fathers Revealed<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Who is there that would not give all his goods to feed the poor,<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> and pour out his gold and silver\n  to the four winds,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> to go where Judge Higbee has gone?<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">That which hath been hid from before the foundation of the world<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> is revealed to babes and\n  sucklings<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> in the last days.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The world is reserved unto burning<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> in the last days. He shall send Elijah the prophet, and he\n  shall reveal the covenants of the fathers in relation to the children, and the covenants of the children\n  in relation to the fathers.<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Four destroying angels<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> holding power over the four quarters of the earth<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> until the servants of\n  God<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> are sealed in their foreheads,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> which signifies sealing the blessing<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span> upon their heads, meaning\n  the everlasting covenant,<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> thereby making their calling and election sure.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> When a seal is put upon\n  the father and mother, it secures their posterity, so that they cannot be lost, but will be saved by\n  virtue of the covenant of their father and mother.<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">To the mourners I would say&mdash;Do as the husband and the father would instruct you, and you\n  shall be reunited.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">The speaker continued to teach the doctrine of election<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> and the sealing powers<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> and\n  principles, and spoke of the doctrine of election with the seed of Abraham,<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> and the sealing of\n  blessings upon his posterity, and the sealing of the fathers and children,<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> according to the\n  declarations of the prophets. He then spoke of Judge Higbee in the world of spirits,<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> and the\n  blessings which he would obtain, and of the kind spirit and disposition of Judge Higbee while living;\n  none of which was reported. (Aug. 13, 1843.) DHC 5:529-531.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">The Priesthood<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">President Smith read the 7th Chap. Hebrews<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> and said: Salem<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> is designed for a Hebrew term.\n  It should be Shiloam, which signifies righteousness and peace; as it is, it is nothing&mdash;neither\n  Hebrew, Greek, Latin, French, nor any other language.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">I say to all those who are disposed to set up stakes for the Almighty, You will come short of the\n  glory of God.<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">To become a joint heir<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> of the heirship of the Son, one must put away<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> all his false traditions.<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"wideEllipse\">* * *<\/p>\n\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108121\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108121)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108121)\">Matt. 19:21<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108559\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108559)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108559)\">Luke 19:8-9<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107422\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107422)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107422)\">Jer. 49:36<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110741\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110741)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110741)\">Rev. 7:1<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115988\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115988)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115988)\">D&amp;C 124:41<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"106638\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 106638)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(106638)\">Ps. 8:2<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108139\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108139)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108139)\">Matt. 21:16<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116169\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116169)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116169)\">D&amp;C 128:18<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107616\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107616)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107616)\">Joel 2:30<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107684\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107684)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107684)\">Zeph. 3:8<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108928\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108928)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108928)\">Acts 2:19<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110561\"><a href=\"ja